ew that there must be only two sexes »for real« stubbornly persists. This heteronormative gender binary is sustained both by science and by visual representations of gender. As objections to such hegemonic knowledge formations, Josh, Hoenes discusses the queer/trans* photographs by Del La Grace Volcano and Loren Cameron and the movie Boys Don't Cry from a transdisciplinary perspective: What potential do cultural and artistic works offer to render gender formations of trans* people more imaginable and livable? And which new narrative possibilities are introduced?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aGender identity. 0aMasculinity in art. 0aMasculinity. 0aTranssexualismxSocial aspects. 0aTranssexuals in motion pictures. 4aBild. 4aDel La Grace Volcano. 4aFilm. 4aFotografie. 4aGender. 4aKunst. 4aKunstgeschichte des 20. Jahrhunderts. 4aKunstwissenschaft. 4aLoren Cameron. 4aQueer Theory. 4aQueere Theorie. 4aTranssexualität. 4aVisuelle Politiken. 4a»Boys Don't Cry«. 7aART / History / Contemporary (1945-).2bisacsh  aArt History of the 20th Century.  aArts.  aFilm.  aFine Arts.  aGender.  aImage.  aPhotography.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts and Architecture 2014z9783110369595oZDB-23-DKA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014z9783111025223oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2014z9783110401226oZDB-23-TGP0 cprintz978383762524040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839425244?locatt=mode:legacy40uht